title: Casters and covers
provenance: Gift of Mr. and Mrs. William M. Cahn, Jr. in memory of Rosalie S. and William M. Cahn
description:
Set of three George I casters. One large, two small casters, each of octagonal, pear-shaped, baluster form on molded foot. Panels of each domed, octagonal cover pierced with alternate scrolls and stylized urns and bouquets; each cover with baluster finial; fitted with bezel closure.
